I stand here before the court today, ready to accept full responsibility for my actions. I deeply regret the choices I have made and the harm it has caused my former boss. I understand that what I have done is inexcusable and a breach of trust.

During my employment at the café, I made the terrible decision to steal money from the cash register. Instead of taking responsibility and addressing my financial difficulties openly, I let greed cloud my judgment. While I only took small amounts each week, this does not lessen the severity of my actions. I deeply apologize for my dishonesty and betrayal.

I want to emphasize that I am a 25-year-old individual with no previous criminal record. Up until this incident, I had always strived to be an honest and law-abiding citizen. However, I recognize that my actions have painted a different picture of who I am. I am genuinely remorseful for tarnishing my character and causing distress to my former boss.

Although I currently do not possess the means to immediately repay the stolen amount due to losing my job, I want to assure the court and my former boss that I am committed to making amends in any way possible. I understand that words alone are insufficient, and I am fully aware of the significant distress I have caused. I am determined to find alternative ways to compensate for the harm I have inflicted.

